	(6696,2157,'_mcb-products','&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h2><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: 13px;\"><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Stella-Bottle-cold-2013_45_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2497\" alt=\"Stella-Bottle-cold-2013_45_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Stella-Bottle-cold-2013_45_165.png\" width=\"45\" height=\"165\" /></a></span></h2>\r\n<h3>Stella Artois</h3>\r\n<h5>LAGER</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 5.2%</h5>\r\nStella Artois was first brewed as a Christmas beer in Leuven. It was named Stella, from the star of Christmas, and Artois after Sebastian Artois, founder of the brewery. It was an instant sensation, and became so popular that it stayed in demand throughout history, and for decades to come. It’s brewed to perfection using the original Stella Artois yeast and the celebrated Saaz hops. It’s the optimum premium lager, with its full flavour and clean crisp taste.  Stella Artois is renowned as a quality beer conditioned for an average of 6 – 11 days longer than most other beers.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Stella-Artois-Cidre-2013_46_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2496\" alt=\"Stella-Artois-Cidre-2013_46_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Stella-Artois-Cidre-2013_46_165.png\" width=\"46\" height=\"165\" /></a>Stella Cidre</h3>\r\n<h5>BELGIAN CIDER</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 5%</h5>\r\nCrisp and refreshing Belgian cider made with hand-picked apples (50%).\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Hoegaarden_witbier_90x_46_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2495\" alt=\"Hoegaarden_witbier_90x_46_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Hoegaarden_witbier_90x_46_165.png\" width=\"46\" height=\"165\" /></a>Hoegaarden</h3>\r\n<h5>WITBIER</h5>\r\n<h5>YEAR ROUND</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 4.9%</h5>\r\nHoegaarden wheat beer has a truly unique heritage. From its humble beginnings in a small provincial village during the Middle Ages, it has grown to become a globally recognized brand, known all over the world as the original Belgian wheat beer.  . When poured, it forms a soft, white creamy head and leaves a generous lacing on the glass. It is naturally cloudy, pale hue shimmers when viewed through the glass.\r\n\r\nWith an aroma of orange peel, coriander and spice, its characteristic taste is entirely unique: smooth, light-bodied, and simultaneously sweet and sour, with a subtle, spiced citrus flavour. Best served in its traditional hexagonal glass.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Spaten_Premium_Lager_70x249_46_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2494\" alt=\"Spaten_Premium_Lager_70x249_46_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Spaten_Premium_Lager_70x249_46_165.png\" width=\"46\" height=\"165\" /></a>Spaten Premium Lager</h3>\r\n<h5>CLASSIC GERMAN PREMIUM LAGER</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 5.2%| IBUS: 21</h5>\r\nSpaten has been a leading exporter of German beer for more than a century. It played a crucial role in establishing the present superior worldwide reputation for German beer. Today people all over the world take pleasure in drinking original Spaten beers, not only in the neighbouring states of France, Austria and Switzerland, but also in Italy, Spain, Scandinavia and the United States. Premium brand, bottom fermented Munchner Lager with a supremely well balanced hop flavor.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Spaten_Oktoberfest_btl_70x269_clr_43_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2493\" alt=\"Spaten_Oktoberfest_btl_70x269_clr_43_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Spaten_Oktoberfest_btl_70x269_clr_43_165.png\" width=\"43\" height=\"165\" /></a>Spaten Octoberfest</h3>\r\n<h5>WORLD\'S FIRST OKTOBERFEST BEER</h5>\r\n<h5>YEAR ROUND</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 5.9%| IBUS: 23</h5>\r\nThe beer of Munich\'s famous Oktoberfest: aromatic, savoury, gold-colored.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Franziskaner_btl_70x266_clr_43_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2491\" alt=\"Franziskaner_btl_70x266_clr_43_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Franziskaner_btl_70x266_clr_43_165.png\" width=\"43\" height=\"165\" /></a>Franziskaner Hefeweisse</h3>\r\n<h5>HEFEWEIZEN</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 5%</h5>\r\nAll of Franziskaner’s weiss beer products are top-fermentation beers noted for their agreeable carbonation levels and zesty wheat flavor. The consistent, high quality products make Franziskaner weiss beers a refreshing taste sensation.\r\n\r\nFranziskaner Hefe-Weisse is noted for its agreeable level of carbonation and its natural cloudiness. It is brewed from wheat malt, barley malt, hops, top-fermenting yeast and water according to a time-honoured Bavarian recipe. Brewed in strict adherence to the Bavarian Purity Law of 1516.\r\n<div></div>\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Franziskaner_Hefe_Dunkel_69x253_clr_45_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2492\" alt=\"Franziskaner_Hefe_Dunkel_69x253_clr_45_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Franziskaner_Hefe_Dunkel_69x253_clr_45_165.png\" width=\"45\" height=\"165\" /></a>Franziskaner  Hefeweisse Dunkel</h3>\r\n<h5>DUNKELWEIZEN</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 5%</h5>\r\nHefe-Weisse Dunkel is top-fermented, noted for agreeable carbonation levels and zesty wheat flavor. The consistently high quality makes Franziskaner weiss beers a refreshing taste sensation . Brewed in strict adherence to the Bavarian Purity Law of 1516.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/leffe-blonde.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2490\" alt=\"leffe blonde\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/leffe-blonde.jpg\" width=\"46\" height=\"163\" /></a>Leffe Blonde</h3>\r\n<h5>BELGIAN ABBEY ALE</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 6.6%</h5>\r\nLeffe beers are  authentic Belgian abbey beers, brewed according to the traditional recipe of the Abbey of Leffe which was founded in 1152. The Norbertine fathers were excited to discover on the site a mineral spring, limpid and pure. In 1240, this water became the basis for Leffe. Leffe Blonde is a dry, fruity, lightly spiced Belgian Abbey Ale, quite full and creamy; a perfect balance of strength and subtlety.\r\n\r\nThe bitterness is delicate, extending over the whole palette and lingering as a subtle aftertaste. Leffe should be served slightly warmer than usual at 41°F to allow its distinct aromatic characteristics to escape and should always be served in its proprietary Chalice glass. Leffe is brewed to the same recipe as it was in 1240.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/bass-pale-ale_45_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2489\" alt=\"bass-pale-ale_45_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/bass-pale-ale_45_165.png\" width=\"45\" height=\"165\" /></a>Bass Pale Ale</h3>\r\n<h5>PALE ALE</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 5%</h5>\r\nBass is the most famous English ale in the world, and has been brewed in Burton, England since 1777. The beer has had an incredible pedigree for centuries. It has been painted by Manet, fought over by Napoleon, and served on the Titanic. Throughout history, it has inspired greatness. The precise combination of Bass Pale Ale and stout resulted in a flavor like no other. Its popularity quickly spread throughout Britain and Ireland, ultimately reaching the United States.\r\n\r\nSo toast history as you pour yourself a Black &amp; Tan, Bass’ distinctive caramel notes with hints of nuts and plum to make it an authentic Black &amp; Tan.'),
