	(2169,1,'2013-11-06 10:33:53','2013-11-06 10:33:53','&nbsp;\r\n\r\nShock Top is a traditional Belgian-Style wheat ale first introduced in 2006 as a seasonal brew under the name Spring Heat Spiced Wheat. After winning a gold medal in 2006 and bronze medal in 2007 in the Belgian White category at the North American Beer Awards, Anheuser-Busch decided that it was only right to bring it to the people year-round. Since calling it Spring Heat didn’t seem to make a whole lot of sense in the middle of November (or July, for that matter), the company changed the name to Shock Top.','Shock Top','.','publish','closed','closed','','shocktop','','','2013-11-10 14:07:04','2013-11-10 14:07:04','',0,'http://cfhq.org/?post_type=project&#038;p=2169',0,'project','',0),
